259
00:17:50,380 --> 00:17:54,620
 Oh Ma Joo is the person who raised Yoon Dong Jin to be the best artist that he is. 

260
00:17:54,620 --> 00:17:57,320
 He was his manager from the very beginning. 

261
00:17:57,320 --> 00:18:00,670
 So that's when you met President Oh Ma Joo. 

262
00:18:00,670 --> 00:18:03,790
 Yes, I'm sick and tired of him. It's been 29 years. 

263
00:18:03,790 --> 00:18:07,700
 Are any of the other members still doing music? 

264
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:10,920
 Nothing. Only one. 

265
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:13,800
 We disbanded pretty soon. 

266
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:16,460
 One of our members got into big trouble. 

267
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:20,150
 Thanks to him, the festival performance was canceled, and the band just disappeared. 

268
00:18:20,150 --> 00:18:23,770
 The only thing that lasted was my relationship with Oh Ma Joo. 

269
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:28,820
 It must've been a serious accident if the band got disbanded. 

270
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:31,790
 It was serious. 

271
00:18:31,790 --> 00:18:35,970
 One of the members got seriously injured because of that. 

272
00:18:35,970 --> 00:18:37,650
- Cheers to scouting him. 
 - Hey, hey.

273
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:39,840
 MJ. 

274
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:41,110
What's wrong?

275
00:18:41,110 --> 00:18:44,600
 Do you remember when that accident happened? 

276
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:47,930
 Of course, I remember very clearly. 

277
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:52,550
 May 1995. The day before the festival. 

278
00:18:52,550 --> 00:18:55,310
 It happened while rehearsing. 

279
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:57,100
 I had forgotten. 

280
00:18:57,100 --> 00:19:02,610
 Yoon Dong Jin was originally a member of Fake First Love Memory-Makers. 

281
00:19:02,610 --> 00:19:04,610
 - And... 
 - What a shame. 

282
00:19:04,610 --> 00:19:09,520
 I have already sent a helper who suits you perfectly. 

283
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:14,550
 If Yoon Dong Jin was the helper Master was referring to... 

284
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:19,020
 If Yoon Dong Jin's interview was a hint to the date of the accident... 

285
00:19:19,020 --> 00:19:25,320
 If the member who got seriously injured during rehearsal was my dad... 

286
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:29,780
I said what's wrong! You're scaring me!

287
00:19:29,780 --> 00:19:31,150
Have something to say to me?

288
00:19:31,150 --> 00:19:34,790
 Dad gets into the accident on the rehearsal day. Tomorrow. 

289
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:41,010
Hey! Where are you going in the middle of a meal?

290
00:19:53,860 --> 00:19:56,770
Answer, please!

291
00:19:56,770 --> 00:19:59,890
You can hear me. Right? You're listening right now. Right?

292
00:19:59,890 --> 00:20:02,510
Is Yoon Dong Jin the helper you were referring to?

293
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:07,510
Is my dad the member who gets injured during the rehearsal tomorrow?

294
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:11,840
Answer me, please!

295
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,730
What's happening tomorrow?

296
00:20:14,730 --> 00:20:16,880
Who gets injured

297
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:20,850
and who causes the accident? Please!

298
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:22,200
Gosh, I'm full.

299
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:24,720
I feel like I'm pregnant with a pig.

300
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:28,100
Let me know when you give birth. I'll hold your hand.

301
00:20:28,100 --> 00:20:32,540
Wow. We finally get to rehearse after all the troubles we went through.

302
00:20:32,540 --> 00:20:35,300
Wow, why am I so nervous about it?

303
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,010
- Just croak if you're scared. 
 - Who said I'm scared?

304
00:20:38,010 --> 00:20:40,740
I'm reaching the boiling point of my passion.

305
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,460
Should we practice again since we had meat?

306
00:20:42,460 --> 00:20:44,940
Should we go to the practice room now?

307
00:20:45,810 --> 00:20:50,610
Nope. Mr. Genius, who's better on stage, is leaving.

308
00:20:51,320 --> 00:20:53,710
Me, too. Bye.

309
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:56,130
Hey.

310
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,860
You're more of a troublemaker than a genius, aren't you?

311
00:20:58,860 --> 00:21:02,550
Sorry. I need to take care of my skin today and tomorrow.

312
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:04,840
I need to sleep so my skin can rejuvenate.

313
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,200
Are you competing to be Miss Korea?

314
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:10,300
I need to look good on stage to be chosen by Se Kyeong.

315
00:21:11,640 --> 00:21:13,170
Hey.

316
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:24,880
 Do Jin will be on parole soon. 

317
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,020
 Be careful at night. 

318
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:29,710
 You might get stabbed in the back. 

319
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,340
Who are you?

320
00:22:06,340 --> 00:22:07,760
I-I'm sorry.

321
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:10,920
I wanted to thank you for last time,

322
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:13,350
but I didn't have the courage.

323
00:22:17,130 --> 00:22:19,490
What are you, fish?

324
00:22:19,490 --> 00:22:21,900
Why do you get tricked so easily?

325
00:22:23,690 --> 00:22:26,100
Thank you so much for last time, Senior.

326
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:30,020
I'll come to the festival to cheer you on. Fighting.

327
00:22:30,020 --> 00:22:32,160
Fighting. Okay.

328
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,200
Go now.

329
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,750
- Okay. 
 - Hurry.

330
00:22:34,750 --> 00:22:37,010
- Okay. 
 - Go, go.

331
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:53,400
Don't worry, Kang Hyeon Yol.

332
00:22:53,400 --> 00:22:55,510
It's not time yet.

333
00:22:55,510 --> 00:23:00,540
It's more fun to step on the flower field when it's in bloom.

334
00:23:07,030 --> 00:23:08,580
You scared me.

335
00:23:08,580 --> 00:23:09,940
What's with you?

336
00:23:09,940 --> 00:23:12,230
Did you see a pig farmer because you were so moved by the pork?

337
00:23:12,230 --> 00:23:13,970
Lee Chan...

338
00:23:13,970 --> 00:23:15,970
I have a favor to ask you.

339
00:23:15,970 --> 00:23:17,420
I hope you do this for me.

340
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:19,150
Stop sounding serious and tell me.

341
00:23:19,150 --> 00:23:22,280
What? You want Grandma's food?

342
00:23:22,280 --> 00:23:24,920
Let's not rehearse tomorrow.

343
00:23:29,460 --> 00:23:33,880
Hey, someone who understands you is over there. Talk to him instead.

344
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:38,180
We've practiced a lot lately.

345
00:23:38,180 --> 00:23:41,750
We won't have any issues at the festival even if we don't rehearse tomorrow.

346
00:23:41,750 --> 00:23:43,120
So...

347
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:45,210
Why do you always do this?

348
00:23:45,210 --> 00:23:47,860
I'm not saying we shouldn't perform.

349
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:49,500
It's just the rehearsal tomorrow—

350
00:23:49,500 --> 00:23:54,510
So why do you want to skip the only rehearsal we get?

351
00:23:54,510 --> 00:23:57,540
There must be a reason why you're doing this.

352
00:23:59,570 --> 00:24:02,750
This isn't something I can explain with words.

353
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:06,860
So, could you just have faith in me and listen to me?

354
00:24:06,860 --> 00:24:10,500
Why? Were you sent from space for a mission?

355
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:12,610
They can conquer the universe if our band fails?

356
00:24:12,610 --> 00:24:15,730
- Lee Chan. 
 - What comes after the rehearsal?

357
00:24:15,730 --> 00:24:17,690
That we shouldn't do the festival?

358
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:19,780
Will you say we should die after that?

359
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:22,300
And I have to trust you and listen to you every time?

360
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:24,860
- Lee Chan. 
 - Don't you have any sense of professionalism?

361
00:24:24,860 --> 00:24:26,670
Gosh, please!

362
00:24:26,670 --> 00:24:30,430
It's just a high school band we started to seduce girls. We aren't pros!

363
00:24:30,430 --> 00:24:32,250
Hey!

364
00:24:36,650 --> 00:24:38,730
Okay.

365
00:24:38,730 --> 00:24:40,290
Let's.

366
00:24:40,290 --> 00:24:42,200
Let's do it.

367
00:24:42,200 --> 00:24:44,190
But...

368
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:48,550
you can't be there. Okay?

369
00:24:48,550 --> 00:24:53,050
We'll figure out the rehearsal on our own tomorrow. Okay?

370
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:56,310
Forget it.

371
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:58,070
I can't listen when you aren't making sense.

372
00:24:58,070 --> 00:25:00,440
Lee Chan, please. Please?

373
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:03,810
Did you know you've always been disloyal to our band?

374
00:25:03,810 --> 00:25:07,950
You pretend to be pure, innocent, and sincere a lot,

375
00:25:07,950 --> 00:25:11,850
but I can tell there was something impure going on.

376
00:25:11,850 --> 00:25:13,790
I was curious, but I never asked you.

377
00:25:13,790 --> 00:25:15,480
I just let you even though I felt nervous.

378
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:18,730
I didn't want the rest of the band to get hurt by stirring things up!

379
00:25:18,730 --> 00:25:22,320
I just! I just let it be pure.

380
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:25,400
But you have to...

381
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:28,690
ruin things...

382
00:25:29,270 --> 00:25:31,760
until the very last minute?

383
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,950
Lee Chan, please. Please?

384
00:25:34,950 --> 00:25:36,800
Fine. Don't do it.

385
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:39,060
You shouldn't do it.

386
00:25:39,060 --> 00:25:41,480
But I will. No matter what.

387
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:44,080
I'll do it no matter what happens!

388
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:49,450
Lee Chan. Lee Chan!

389
00:25:49,450 --> 00:25:52,210
Open the door for a second!

390
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:09,950
 What do I do? How do I stop him? 

391
00:26:09,950 --> 00:26:11,530
 How will I make him? 

392
00:26:11,530 --> 00:26:13,840
 Should I lock him up? Tie him up? 

393
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:18,450
 Make him faint? Kidnap him? Or... 

394
00:26:23,220 --> 00:26:27,520
He's in his mid-40s if he's the same age as Mom.

395
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:30,770
He must've changed drastically with the passage of time.

396
00:26:30,770 --> 00:26:33,520
He must have a gut and hair loss by default.

397
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:37,330
And he might wear toe socks because of athlete's foot.

398
00:26:37,330 --> 00:26:39,710
His pores must be as large as a stadium

399
00:26:39,710 --> 00:26:43,100
and oil must flow out of them, too.

400
00:26:44,300 --> 00:26:46,900
The reality hit.

401
00:26:46,900 --> 00:26:49,710
I feel so put off now.

402
00:27:03,960 --> 00:27:05,220
Who's this?

403
00:27:05,220 --> 00:27:07,020
 It's me, Ha Eun Gyeol. 

404
00:27:07,020 --> 00:27:11,360
 Could we talk for a second if you don't mind? 

405
00:27:19,710 --> 00:27:21,670
My gosh...

406
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:42,890
I was sleeping. What's this about?

407
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:44,640
I'm sorry to bother you at night.

408
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:46,050
I came to ask you a favor.

409
00:27:46,050 --> 00:27:49,150
- I really need you to do this for me. 
 - I see...

410
00:27:49,150 --> 00:27:51,180
But you came empty-handed.

411
00:27:51,180 --> 00:27:55,480
Have manners and come with an armful of stuff.

412
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,480
Please help me!

413
00:28:01,110 --> 00:28:03,330
It's something only you can do.

414
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,910
I beg you.

415
00:28:12,010 --> 00:28:14,080
Newspaper.

416
00:28:28,420 --> 00:28:32,570
 Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore! 

417
00:28:32,570 --> 00:28:34,420
 Encore! Encore! 

418
00:28:34,420 --> 00:28:36,980
 Encore! Encore! Encore! 

419
00:28:36,980 --> 00:28:38,680
 Encore! Encore! 

420
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:42,090
 Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore! 

421
00:28:42,090 --> 00:28:46,290
 Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore... 

422
00:28:50,750 --> 00:28:52,890
 Se Kyeong! 

423
00:28:52,890 --> 00:28:55,300
 Se Kyeong! 

424
00:28:55,300 --> 00:28:57,550
 Se Kyeong, you came. 

425
00:29:08,060 --> 00:29:09,810
 Choose one! 

426
00:29:09,810 --> 00:29:14,580
 Choose one! Choose one! Choose one! 

427
00:29:14,580 --> 00:29:17,260
 I came to keep the promise I made to you. 

428
00:29:17,260 --> 00:29:20,950
 Se Kyeong, I'll respect whatever decision you make. 

429
00:29:20,950 --> 00:29:24,400
 Se Kyeong, it's me. Right? You'll choose me. Right? 

430
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,390
 I choose... 

431
00:29:31,420 --> 00:29:33,020
 Say, Lee Chan. 

432
00:29:34,630 --> 00:29:36,720
 Tell me, Se Kyeong. 

433
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:39,140
 Answer the phone. 

434
00:29:39,140 --> 00:29:40,670
 What? 

435
00:29:42,550 --> 00:29:44,290
 Answer the phone, I said. 

436
00:29:44,290 --> 00:29:47,060
 Lee Chan, answer the phone! 

437
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:49,510
Geez...

438
00:29:49,510 --> 00:29:52,600
 Lee Chan! Please! 

439
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:55,740
 Gosh, Lee Chan! Lee Chan! 

440
00:29:56,470 --> 00:29:59,550
 Lee Chan, please! 

441
00:30:03,430 --> 00:30:04,640
Hello?

442
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:08,750
I'm sorry. I woke you up. This is Se Kyeong.

443
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:13,540
Se Kyeong. What made you call so early?

444
00:30:13,540 --> 00:30:15,940
The thing is...

445
00:30:15,940 --> 00:30:17,860
I'm in a bit of a tricky situation.

446
00:30:17,860 --> 00:30:20,530
What? What? What? What's wrong? What's going on?

447
00:30:20,530 --> 00:30:22,110
Are you sick? Did you get hurt?

448
00:30:22,110 --> 00:30:23,570
No, it's not that.

449
00:30:23,570 --> 00:30:27,080
You know the individual photo cards we're handing out with the pamphlet at the festival?

450
00:30:27,080 --> 00:30:28,490
Yes.

451
00:30:28,490 --> 00:30:30,630
What about them?

452
00:30:30,630 --> 00:30:33,320
Everyone looks good,

453
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:37,140
but yours is a bit... How should I say...

454
00:30:39,170 --> 00:30:41,080
Let me be honest.

455
00:30:41,080 --> 00:30:44,700
I'm so upset that your charm doesn't come across at all.

456
00:30:45,660 --> 00:30:47,040
Gosh, you scared me.

457
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,640
I'm okay, Se Kyeong.

458
00:30:48,640 --> 00:30:50,640
I look the best in person.

459
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:53,610
I know, but I wanted to keep one if it turned out well.

460
00:30:53,610 --> 00:30:55,460
My gosh.

461
00:30:55,460 --> 00:30:57,210
Keep one?

462
00:30:57,210 --> 00:31:00,500
- My photo? 
 - Yes. I was going to laminate it, too.

463
00:31:00,500 --> 00:31:03,480
 So I'm thinking of retaking yours. 

464
00:31:03,480 --> 00:31:04,930
That'd be too difficult. Right?

465
00:31:04,930 --> 00:31:08,910
No, not at all! I can do it! Yes! No matter what!

466
00:31:08,910 --> 00:31:12,990
Really? What a relief. I worried you might say no.

467
00:31:12,990 --> 00:31:16,470
By the way, I only have time today. Is it okay to skip school?

468
00:31:16,470 --> 00:31:18,100
Yes, of course.

469
00:31:18,100 --> 00:31:22,870
The school will be there even if I skip for a day.

470
00:31:25,420 --> 00:31:27,160
Well, oh...

471
00:31:28,340 --> 00:31:29,940
Right, by the way, today—

472
00:31:29,940 --> 00:31:32,260
I know. You have a rehearsal at 3:00. Right?

473
00:31:32,260 --> 00:31:34,050
I'm sure you'll be able to make it.

474
00:31:34,050 --> 00:31:35,560
Really?

475
00:31:39,630 --> 00:31:41,150
Where should I meet you?

476
00:31:41,150 --> 00:31:43,170
Where can I meet you?

477
00:32:08,950 --> 00:32:12,640
 There's an island called Boreum. It's not far from Incheon. 

478
00:32:22,010 --> 00:32:23,790
Here.

479
00:32:23,790 --> 00:32:26,320
Let me carry it for you.

480
00:32:27,090 --> 00:32:29,170
You should've told me you had all this.

481
00:32:29,170 --> 00:32:31,390
I'll carry this for you, too.

482
00:32:31,390 --> 00:32:32,490
Gosh, thank you.

483
00:32:32,490 --> 00:32:34,910
Where are you going?

484
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:38,090
   

485
00:32:44,230 --> 00:32:45,820
I'm from Seoul.

486
00:32:45,820 --> 00:32:47,240
Yes, from Seoul.

487
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:48,860
Gosh, thank you.

488
00:32:48,860 --> 00:32:51,340
 I found an amazing place that could capture 

489
00:32:51,340 --> 00:32:56,330
 your boyish, mischievous, and tough side of you, too. 

490
00:32:56,330 --> 00:33:00,240
 I'll set up the camera and wait for you. Don't be late. 

491
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:04,120
Se Kyeong! I'm here!

492
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:07,550
Wait for just a moment!

493
00:33:07,550 --> 00:33:11,520
 Wait for just a moment! 

494
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:15,380
 Se Kyeong! I'm here! 

495
00:33:15,380 --> 00:33:19,260
 Wait for just a moment! 

496
00:33:19,260 --> 00:33:21,950
 Se Kyeong! 

497
00:33:21,950 --> 00:33:26,150
Gosh, this is why you can't live with guilt.

498
00:33:31,960 --> 00:33:35,650
 Why do I have to trick Lee Chan like that? 

499
00:33:35,650 --> 00:33:38,500
Someone's life is at stake. It's important.

500
00:33:38,500 --> 00:33:42,480
It's too vague. I'm not convinced. Give me another reason.

501
00:33:44,880 --> 00:33:46,650
I have a secret I can't talk about.

502
00:33:46,650 --> 00:33:49,020
You already told me when we went to the theme park.

503
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:50,490
That won't work. Another one.

504
00:33:50,490 --> 00:33:53,800
Don't be like that. Can't you please help me? Please.

505
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:56,830
Another reason.

506
00:34:13,460 --> 00:34:16,200
Okay. I'll help you.

507
00:34:16,200 --> 00:34:18,800
I don't need words to understand the message.

508
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:22,540
I can feel your desperation, urgency, and goodwill without bad intentions.

509
00:34:22,540 --> 00:34:25,900
Really? Will you really help me?

510
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:29,030
You said someone's life is at stake, and it's important.

511
00:34:29,030 --> 00:34:31,310
I could tell you weren't completely joking.

512
00:34:31,310 --> 00:34:35,840
"I can't ignore someone's desperate situation because it looks trivial to me.

513
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:39,800
I know what it's like to be in a situation you can't talk about."

514
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:44,000
That's what you said at the jokbal place. I'm doing it for the same reason.

515
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:47,420
Thank you. Thank you so much. I'll make sure to return this favor—

516
00:34:47,420 --> 00:34:48,830
